</P>
<P>
   OBIT-DIMAGGIO (Undated) _ Joe DiMaggio, the flawless center
fielder for the New York Yankees who, along with Babe Ruth and
Mickey Mantle, symbolized the team's dynastic greatness across the
20th century and whose 56-game hitting streak in 1941 made him an
instant and indelible American folk hero, has died. By Joseph
Durso. (The obit has moved in ``a'' news file.)
