   &UR; By Maria Cianci &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; BOOKS-Irish  &LR; _ Today's Irish table offers a lot
more sophistication than corned beef and cabbage, say two new
books: ``The Irish Heritage Cookbook,'' by Margaret M. Johnson, an
American who grew up in an Irish Catholic community in
Massachusetts; and ``West of Ireland Summers; a Cookbook,'' by
British television producer/food writer Tamasin Day-Lewis. Expect
traditional Irish potato dishes colcannon and champ, but don't be
surprised to find ceviche or Poulet Vall &LR; e &LR; e d'Auge.
</P>
<P>
   With recipes.
