<P>
   &UR; RJR NABISCO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RJR-NABISCO-BREAKUP (Undated) _ RJR Nabisco Holdings is breaking
itself up. Bowing to shareholder pressure, it will spin off its
American tobacco business from its Nabisco food unit, in which it
holds an 80.6 percent stake. In addition, it will sell its
international tobacco operations to Japan Tobacco for $8 billion in
cash, which RJR will use to help pay down the $6.4 billion in debt
that its worldwide tobacco business has amassed, some of it from
defending against and settling lawsuits. By Constance L. Hays.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   With these sidebars:
</P>
