   &UR; OTHER FINANCIAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   AHOLD-PATHMARK (Undated) _ Royal Ahold, the Dutch company that
owns Giant Food and already records more than half of its sales in
the United States, buys Pathmark Stores of New Jersey. Ahold will
acquire the stock of SMG-II Holdings, a holding company that
controls Pathmark through its Supermarket General Holdings unit,
for $250 million. It will assume about $1.5 billion in Pathmark
debt. It also posts a profit gain. By Dana Canedy.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Undated) _ Folo reports that Microsoft and
the Justice Department are exploring ways to settle the antitrust
case.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-TRAVEL (Undated) _ In software, Microsoft is the
gorilla whose every thundering step shakes the industry. But in the
on-line travel business, it is just another money-losing upstart.
And so at the same time that Microsoft is wrestling the Justice
Department in a landmark antitrust suit, it is also asking the
federal regulators to file an antitrust action against the nation's
airlines.
</P>
<P>
   INTEL-ANTITRUST (Undated) _ More about the proposed antitrust
settlement between the FTC and Intel.
</P>
<P>
   FLUOR-CUTBACK (Los Angeles) _ Fluor, the engineering and
construction company, plans to eliminate 5,000 jobs and close 15
offices. By Andrew Pollack.
</P>
<P>
