   CAMBODIA-TRIAL (Bangkok, Thailand) _ Ta Mok, the Khmer Rouge
strongman, will become the first member of the Khmer Rouge to face
trial. He has been charged under a 1994 law banning the leftist
group. Hun Sen, the prime minister, says Ta Mok will be tried in
Cambodia. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
