mothballs, Lamar Alexander announces his presidential candidacy
again. By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   LABOR-COIA (Undated) _ After a two-year investigation, a former
federal prosecutor acting as in-house judge clears Arthur Coia,
president of the laborers' union and a Clinton buddy, of ties to
organized crime, but fines him $100,000 for improper dealings with
a friend who leased cars to the union. Republicans expected to be
outraged. By Steven Greenhouse.
</P>
