the Palm Beacher accused of kidnapping his children years ago and
then setting up a double life. (Holland, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   FLA-EVICTION _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Few men are so defined by
location as sun-worn 67-year-old Clifton Lirette. When Lirette
first settled here 20 years ago, a sign across U.S. 27 read: ``Deem
City, Pop. 2.'' Then a fire destroyed the convenience store and
service station and, for practical purposes, Deem City ceased to
be. Yet Lirette remained at his remote outpost at the edge of the
Everglades in southwestern Palm Beach County, 100 yards from the
Broward line. Now the county wants Lirette to move himself off the
land. (Moffett, Palm Beach Post) 34 inches. MOVED.
</P>
