   It's not only big developers who resent the extremely popular
environmental movement. Farmers are becoming increasingly angry
about it. Farmers across the country are at odds with
environmentalists over several issues, including the disposal of
animal waste and the banning of widely used pesticides. (Main
article includes 2 color photos)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: ENVIRONMENT-GORE: The conflict between farmers and
environmental groups has put Vice President Al Gore into a bit of a
pickle. Known and praised as an environmentalist, Gore is starting
to realize it is not politically wise to antagonize farmers.
(Includes 1 color photo of Gore)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: ENVIRONMENT-WEB: Environmentalists are increasingly using
the Internet to support their causes.
</P>
