<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-GUILLEN _ Shortstop Ozzie Guillen continues to play
well for the Braves, who play the Mets Tuesday. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 13-15.
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-LEWIS _ NEW YORK _ Name any of the top heavyweights of this
era and Lennox Lewis hasn't fought any of them. Now when he fights
one, everything is on the line. Evander Holyfield and Lewis meet
Saturday night at Madison Square Garden to unify the heavyweight
title. Lewis still has his skeptics. (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ARCHDEACON-COLUMN _ NEW YORK _ It was a classic moment of
give-and-take in what many consider the greatest single sporting
event of this half-century. Joe Frazier _ head down, body low,
bobbing and weaving incessantly _ bore in on Muhammad Ali with a
remorseless body attack that was climaxed by searing hooks to the
ribs. In response, Ali fired a series of jabs, landed some stinging
right hands and then shouted at his stumpy nemesis: ``Fray-sha,
don't you know, I am God?'' ``God, you're in the wrong place
tonight,'' Frazier shot back. Columnist Tom Archdeacon remembers an
unforgettable night 28 years ago. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
