Louise Woodward turned over brain tissue from Matthew Eappen to a
free-lance journalist whose report became the basis for last
Sunday's ``60 Minutes'' program. By Yvonne Abraham, Don Aucoin and
Shelley Murphy. 1000 words. (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   HARVARD-RAPE (Cambridge, Mass.) _ With scores of protesters
outside, undergraduate faculty votes on whether to expel
permanently a student accused of date rape. By Kate Zernike. 700
words.
</P>
<P>
   ATHLETES-SATS (Undated) _ As court tosses out use of minimum SAT
scores in admitting student athletes, coaches applaud the move.
Academia decries it. By Kate Zernike and Mark Blaudschun. 1200
words. (a and s coding)
</P>
<P>
   FLU-VACCINE (Undated) _ Broader use of flu vaccine could prevent
needless hospitalizations and deaths among people with chronic
illnesses, and could also reduce absenteeism among health care
workers, new studies say. By Richard Saltus. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   SOLAR-TELESCOPE (Undated) _ New telescope method predicts major
