<SLUG> BC-FBN-PATRIOTS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHIGHAM TO VISIT JACKSONVILLE, MIAMI 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NICK CAFARDO  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Patriots safety/special teams player Larry Whigham, an
unrestricted free agent who hasn't received an offer from New
England, will make visits to Jacksonville tomorrow and Miami
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Whigham, a high-energy player, has been told by coach Pete
Carroll that he is wanted back. However, Whigham also was told that
if he receives a sizable offer, it might be in his best interest to
take it rather than wait for the Patriots.
</P>
<P>
   The Patriots continue to explore kicking options and have
veteran Norm Johnson on the back burner in case they lose Adam
Vinatieri.
</P>
<P>
   Running back Travis Jervey, whom the Patriots have expressed
interest in, is close to signing with the San Francisco 49ers,
while Darick Holmes is visiting Kansas City today.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
