   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Although Republicans have largely
agreed with President Clinton's plan to set aside part of the
anticipated budget surplus to shore up Social Security, they still
face challenges in devising an investment-based plan for the
retirement system. Letting individuals invest a portion of their
Social Security funds in the stock market while still guaranteeing
minimum benefits could be tricky, critics say. By BENNETT ROTH.
(Already filed.)
