<HEADLINE>
BIOGRAPHICAL FACTS ON LAMAR ALEXANDER 
</HEADLINE>
  (With ALEXANDER-POLITICS) 
(nk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Biographical facts on Lamar Alexander, who declared his
candidacy for the Republican presidential nomination on Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
   CURRENT JOB: Sits on several corporate boards.
</P>
<P>
   BORN: July 3, 1940, in Knoxville, Tenn.
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION: Maryville High School, Maryville, Tenn., 1958;
Vanderbilt University, B.A., 1962; New York University, J.D., 1965.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION: Presbyterian.
</P>
<P>
   MILITARY SERVICE: None.
</P>
<P>
   MARRIED: Leslee Buhler in 1969.
</P>
<P>
   CHILDREN: Andrew, 29, Leslee, 26, Kathryn, 24, William, 19.
</P>
<P>
   GOVERNMENT POSITIONS: Legislative assistant to Sen. Howard
Baker, R-Tenn., 1967-68; assistant in the White House Office of
Congressional Relations, 1969-70; Governor of Tennessee, 1979-87;
Secretary of Education, 1991-93.
</P>
<P>
   OTHER MAJOR POSITIONS: Private law practice, 1971-78; president,
University of Tennessee, 1988-91; private law practice, 1993-95.
</P>
</TEXT>
