c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``I really didn't want to expose this _ and I'm attached to the
country, the Party, the people. But we are at a critical juncture _
the medicine we have is about to run out _ and I have to think
about my child.''
</P>
<P>
   _SONG XISHAN, a Chinese man who is trying to force the hospital
or government to pay for his son's HIV medication.
</P>
