   (NYT25) BEIJING -- March 09, 1999 -- CHINA-AIDS-2, 3-09 -- Song
Pengfei, 17, who contracted the HIV virus after a blood
transfusion, poses with his parents. The family is fighting to get
money to pay for Song's treatment. Song is one of a small but
growing number of Chinese infected with the H.I.V virus in a
country that is emotionally, financially and medically largely
unprepared to deal with them. (Elisabeth Rosenthal/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
