<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXYNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUIJANO ASSIGNED TO GALAXY'S PROJECT-40 LIST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Major League Soccer assigned Rio Hondo College
standout Marvin Quijano to the Los Angeles Galaxy's Project-40 list
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Quijano, 19, scored 24 goals in 30 games for the Roadrunners
last season. The forward impressed Los Angeles coach Octavio
Zambrano during preseason training.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Galaxy is always interested in finding talented players
who can compete at the professional level,'' Zambrano said. ``The
Project-40 evaluation was designed to identify some of the top
young prospects in the region, and Marvin certainly is a top
prospect.''
</P>
<P>
   A native of El Salvador, Quijano joined the Galaxy in February
after participating in an invitation-only evaluation held at the
Rose Bowl. He has since appeared in five preseason games, scoring
two goals and notching an assist.
</P>
<P>
   Project-40 signees earn the minimum MLS salary and are awarded a
five-year academic package covering tuition by the United States
Soccer Federation.
</P>
<P>
   -- The Galaxy returned from Guadalajara on Sunday after running
its exhibition record to 7-0-2 with a 5-1 victory over Atlas of the
Mexican first division.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday, the Galaxy suffered its first loss of the season, 2-0,
in an exhibition against the U.S. national team at UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   ``We looked pretty good, actually,'' Zambrano said.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a tight match throughout,'' Zambrano said. ``We hit the
post a couple of times. Overall, though, it was just a great test
for us because of their speed of play. We haven't been tested that
much during the preseason, so this game really helped our
preparation.''
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. team is in Southern California preparing for the U.S.
Cup on Thursday (against Guatemala).
</P>
<P>
   -- The Galaxy plays at Cal State Fullerton tonight at 7:30.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
